article_title: Examining Plummeting Obamacare Enrollment Projections, Part II

article_metadata.author: The Apothecary

og.description: This article shows that the economic models of the ACA projected far too many people without subsidies would enroll in exchange plans and discusses reasons to be skeptical that the individual mandate will lead as many people to purchase coverage as widely assumed.
